    <name>
      <text>28.2.1.6 unit vector normal to sphere</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Find a unit vector which is normal to the sphere \(({@x+ aa@})^2+({@y+bb@})^2+({@z+cc@})^2={@size@}\) at the point \((0,0,0).\) </p>
<p>[[input:ans1]]\(\underline{i} +\)[[input:ans2]]\(\underline{j} +\)[[input:ans3]]\(\underline{k}\) [[validation:ans1]] [[validation:ans2]] [[validation:ans3]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>We let \(\phi=({@x+ aa@})^2+({@y+bb@})^2+({@z+cc@})^2={@size@}\), and then calculate the following vector field as: \[\underline{\nabla} \phi = 2({@x+ aa@})\underline{i}+2({@y+bb@})\underline{j}+2({@z+cc@})\underline{k}\]</p>

<p>The value that this vector field takes at the point \((0,0,0)\) is \(\underline{\nabla} \phi (0,0,0)= {@val_vec_field@}\) which is a vector normal to the sphere.</p>

<p>Dividing this vector by its magnitude forms a unit vector: \( \displaystyle {@unit_vec@}\).]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
